&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Abstract:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In the current scenario when online teaching has become&lt;br /&gt;inevitable, faculty are experimenting with various&lt;br /&gt;technologies to teach online. Tools like Moodle, WebEx,&lt;br /&gt;Edmodo, Google Classrooms, Canvas, GoToMeeting,&lt;br /&gt;Zoom, Mentimeter etc are being used by the faculty. It&lt;br /&gt;requires time to explore these tools and to choose the&lt;br /&gt;best tool suitable for a particular type of class.&lt;br /&gt;This webinar aims at providing the faculty with insights&lt;br /&gt;into some of the technologies available that can be used&lt;br /&gt;for conducting online classes. This session shall empower&lt;br /&gt;the faculty with the essential knowledge required to use&lt;br /&gt;these technologies as well as to select a tool based on the&lt;br /&gt;requirement.&lt;br /&gt;Tools to be covered:&lt;br /&gt;1. Moodle&lt;br /&gt;2. Google Classrooms&lt;br /&gt;3. Edmodo&lt;br /&gt;4. Mentimeter&lt;br /&gt;5. Canvas&lt;br /&gt;6. Zoom&lt;br /&gt;7. WebEx&lt;br /&gt;8. GoToMeeting&lt;/p&gt;
