&lt;p&gt;Education today has to cater to the large volume of students or learners spread across many domains and multiple geographies. &amp;nbsp;Differences in student skills, physical infrastructure that &amp;nbsp;colleges can provide, &amp;nbsp;teaching skills of faculty &amp;nbsp;etc, are challenges. ICT has been a buzz word and is often seen as a panacea for meeting this variety. &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Traditional education models for Sciences or Engineering have had a mix of class room teaching and doing &amp;nbsp;experiments in physical laboratories to gain a practical understanding of the concepts learnt. This model has worked well in the past, but with &amp;nbsp;the growing volumes, availability of trained faculty and fast changing curricula, &amp;nbsp;online virtual labs and experiments have become necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To address this scenario, the MHRD, has created a repo of &amp;nbsp;about 1400 virtual experiments (http://vlab.co.in/ ) in commonly known engineering and science domains, that are available to all students and faculty. These were built by a consortium of &amp;nbsp;12 leading Institutes in India. These &amp;nbsp;Virtual Labs are accessible from anywhere globally on laptops or mobiles on most &amp;nbsp;browsers via internet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These Virtual Labs are complete Learning Management Systems and are used by faculty to teach with ease and by students to practice &amp;nbsp;them &amp;nbsp;as they like. &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Today over 8 lakhs participants &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;have used it in India and a smaller number in the rest of the world. In today&amp;rsquo;s Lockdown scenario, the usage of these labs has grown in multiples.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This &amp;nbsp;session titled &#39;Virtual &amp;nbsp;labs for Science and Engineering&#39;, is intended to give you an overview of these labs. Importantly, the need for faculty to use labs with the right (teaching) pedagogies is stressed. A sample demo of the virtual labs is also included.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Women are an integral part of society and face multiple challenges in every role of their life. It can be at home, office or anywhere else. Even during this struggling times of COVID -19, women are not only looking after the families but also completing their professional commitments too. It is very challenging to accomplish multiple jobs simultaneously.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To understand the concerns of women and help them overcome the stress, IEEE Women in Engineering Affinity Group, Hyderabad Section in association with IEEE Education Society is organizing a Panel Discussion with eminent personalities on &amp;ldquo;Work from home and its challenges&amp;rdquo; on 25&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;April 2020 from 5.00 to 6.30 PM.&lt;/p&gt;
