&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Webinar on&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;Content Delivery Using Moodle and Canvas&quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Abstract&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Online teaching requires tools that can enable the teacher to teach, disseminate information to the students, monitor student participation, and also evaluate the students learning. On the other hand, the learner also requires tools which can provide easy access to the resources provided by the teacher, should be able to learn online, and perform classroom activities like submissions, discussions, assessments, etc online.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Many tools have come up in the recent past owing to the increase in demand for online teaching. Some of such tools have been covered in our earlier Webinar on &amp;lsquo;Tools for Teaching Online&amp;rsquo;. This session shall cover two such tools &amp;lsquo;Canvas&amp;rsquo; and &amp;lsquo;Moodle&amp;rsquo; which provide a complete learning management system required for a teacher to teach online&lt;/p&gt;
