&lt;p&gt;According to World Health Organization, Assistive devices and technologies are those whose primary purpose is to maintain or improve an individual&amp;rsquo;s functioning and independence to facilitate participation and to enhance overall well-being. They can also help prevent impairments and secondary health conditions. Examples of assistive devices and technologies include wheelchairs, prostheses, hearings aids, visual aids, and specialized computer software and hardware that increase mobility, hearing, vision, or communication capacities. Assistive Technology Centre of&amp;nbsp; Excellence was established at Shri Vishnu Engineering College for Women in technical collaboration with University of Massachusetts, Lowell, USA with a sole purpose to ignite the young minds of its students towards innovating assistive technology solutions to aid the differently people, Over the last decade, many affordable innovative solutions have come out of this lab which not only are recognized across India for their creativity and usefulness, but also are being distributed to the beneficiaries&amp;nbsp; for free of cost thus serving the purpose of its establishment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This webinar focuses on the development of few such assistive devices that help the differently abled people.&lt;/p&gt;
